{
  "stem": "25773.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They just, just embarked on your place, and-- but the feeling of security was tremendous, because we children never felt-- there was not this dreadful feeling of taking drugs, which is, to my mind, lack of security and break of the family.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in Jewish families, it was a bastion of strength, the Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We shared bar mitzvahs, and weddings and all kinds of-- simchat.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we had, sometimes, unhappiness, or sometimes adventures, or was sometimes scandalous things.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But it was all dealt within the family unit.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it was a blessing, because a child-- if mother and father was not at home, they went to the auntie, then went to the grandmother.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And a feeling of security was a very prominent aspect of, of, of our Jewish life.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had the, the, we had the melamed, called melamed--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--Who, my father-- it means a teacher who insisted-- he came over to teach us Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were very naughty.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Sometimes we hid under the table and under the-- behind the cupboards, and we didn't want to.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't want to because it was a different language.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we children felt, we want-- we don't want-- but I did learn my alphabet then and there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And have a vague way.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, of course, I can, I can, I can read the prayers and, and, and, a bit of modern Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I tried many times.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mostly Jewish.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Jewish people in Poland-- it was a special feature.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Jewish people of Poland were-- you know, they-- many of them who lived in the predominantly Jewish precinct, they, they, even-- many of them didn't speak Polish.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They spoke only, only Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We, at home, spoke, of course, Polish, because this was the languages my father also needed.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
